  "response": "Hair typically grows at an average rate of about half an inch (1.25 cm) per month, or approximately 6 inches (15 cm) per year. After completely shaving one's head, the regrowth process follows this general timeline:\n\n1. First 2-4 weeks: Very short, stubble-like growth\n2. 1-3 months: Hair reaches about 1-2 inches in length\n3. 6 months: Hair grows to around 3-4 inches\n4. 12 months: Hair can reach 6-8 inches depending on individual factors\n\nFactors affecting hair growth rate include:\n- Genetics\n- Age\n- Overall health\n- Nutrition\n- Hormones\n- Gender (men typically grow hair slightly faster)\n\nIndividual growth rates can vary, and some people might experience faster or slower hair growth. Additionally, factors like hair type, ethnicity, and personal health can influence the speed and thickness of hair regrowth.",
